This profile assumes:
- systemd and nss-systemd are present on the base system
- pam_env.so, pam_unix.so, pam_deny.so, pam_pwquality.so, pam_limits.so, pam_systemd.so, and pam_umask.so are available
- pam_lastlog2.so is available if you want the optional postlogin last-login update
- local account data lives in /etc/passwd, /etc/group, /etc/shadow, and /etc/gshadow
